An automated AI infrustructured workflow for Real Estate Companies (and relevant) built with n8n and Supabase to streamline real estate lead processing, filtering, and management.

Features:
1. Automated Lead Fetching: Captures incoming real estate inquiries via Webhooks/APIs using the info from Supabase.
2. AI-Powered Filtering: Uses OpenAI/Claude to analyze buyer requirements after automated handful conversations with them and filter high-quality leads based on intent and budget.
3. Information Collecting: Collects necessary information from client if he/she wills to proceed.
4. Site Visit Managament: COnfirms at exact time and date if any client wants to visit site, checks availability from company calender and books a time slot.
5. Database Update: Only after that, this AI powered automated system updates the Lead_Capture table in database with collected informations.
6. Management Team notification: After the 4th stage, it sendns a notification message as a lead_capture to the Telegram (or else) group where any of the assigned officials come to deal with that client.

Tech Stack:
1. Workflow Orchestration: n8n 
2. Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL)
3. AI Engine: OpenAI API
4. Instruction Method: Advanced Prompt Engineering
5. Language: javascript (sometimes Python) and json (inititially)                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                          
Follow this route to use:
1. Download the `real-estate-mega-infrustructre.json` file from this repository.
2. Import it into your **n8n** instance.
3. Configure your Supabase credentials and OpenAI API keys in the respective nodes.
4. Set up the webhook trigger to start receiving real estate leads automatically.
                                                                                                                          
